      "review_summary": "The PR changes memory-core FTS indexing to prefix chunk text with the memory path, strips that prefix from keyword snippets/scoring, versions the FTS text format, self-heals legacy indexes, and adds regression tests.\n\nPR surface: Source +99, Tests +324. Total +423 across 7 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level. Current main stores paths as UNINDEXED FTS metadata and writes only chunk body text into the indexed FTS column, matching the linked filename/date-token miss.",
